Calculates and returns active stake for address
     * Active stake = (active deployer stake + active delegator stake)
     active deployer stake = (direct deployer stake - locked deployer stake)
         locked deployer stake = amount of pending decreaseStakeRequest for address
     active delegator stake = (total delegator stake - locked delegator stake)
         locked delegator stake = amount of pending undelegateRequest for address

evaluateProposalOutcome(uint256).details: Requires that caller is an active staker at the time the proposal is created

getProposalTargetContractHash(uint256).details: This is a separate function because the getProposalById returns too many variables already and by adding more, you get the error `InternalCompilerError: Stack too deep, try using fewer variables`

params._voter: - address of the voter we want to check

getVoteInfoByProposalAndVoter(uint256,ad.return: returns vote direction and magnitude if valid vote, else default values

params._callData: - encoded value(s) to call function with if proposal is successful
params._callValue: - amount of wei if a token transfer is involved
params._functionSignature: - function signature of the function to be executed if proposal is successful
params._targetContractRegistryKey: - key in registry of target contract

inProgressProposalsAreUpToDate().details: Is public since its called internally in `submitProposal()` as well as externally in UI

initialize(address,uint256,uint256,uint2.details: _votingPeriod <= DelegateManager.undelegateLockupDurationstakingAddress must be initialized separately after Staking contract is deployed

params._executionDelay: - number of blocks that must pass after votingPeriod has expired before proposal can be evaluated/executed
params._guardianAddress: - address of account that has special Governance permissions
params._maxInProgressProposals: - max number of InProgress proposals possible at once
params._registryAddress: - address of the registry proxy contract
params._votingPeriod: - period in blocks for which a governance proposal is open for voting
params._votingQuorumPercent: - required minimum percentage of total stake to have voted to consider a proposal valid

submitProposal(bytes32,uint256,string,by.details: _name and _description length is not enforced since they aren't stored on-chain and only event emitted

params._callData: - encoded value(s) to call function with if proposal is successful
params._callValue: - amount of wei to pass with function call if a token transfer is involved
params._description: - Text description of proposal to be emitted in event
params._functionSignature: - function signature of the function to be executed if proposal is successful
params._name: - Text name of proposal to be emitted in event
params._targetContractRegistryKey: - Registry key for the contract concerning this proposal

params._proposalId: - id of the proposal this vote is for
params._vote: - can be either {Yes, No} from Vote enum. No other values allowed

params._proposalId: - id of the proposal this vote is for
params._vote: - can be either {Yes, No} from Vote enum. No other values allowed

evaluateProposalOutcome(uint256).notice: Once the voting period + executionDelay for a proposal has ended, evaluate the outcome and     execute the proposal if voting quorum met & vote passes.     To pass, stake-weighted vote must be > 50% Yes.

getInProgressProposals().notice: Get the array of all InProgress proposal Ids

getMaxInProgressProposals().notice: Get the max number of concurrent InProgress proposals

getProposalById(uint256).notice: Get proposal information by proposal Id

getProposalTargetContractHash(uint256).notice: Get proposal target contract hash by proposalId

getVoteInfoByProposalAndVoter(uint256,ad.notice: Get vote direction and vote magnitude for a given proposal and voter

getVotingQuorumPercent().notice: Get the contract voting quorum percent

guardianExecuteTransaction(bytes32,uint2.notice: Allows the guardianAddress to execute protocol actions

inProgressProposalsAreUpToDate().notice: Returns false if any proposals in inProgressProposals array are evaluatable         Evaluatable = proposals with closed votingPeriod

initialize().notice: wrapper function around parent contract Initializable's `initializable` modifier     initializable modifier ensures this function can only be called once by each deployed child contract     sets isInitialized flag to true to which is used by _requireIsInitialized()

isGovernanceAddress().notice: Used to check if is governance contract before setting governance address in other contracts

setExecutionDelay(uint256).notice: Set the execution delay for a proposal

setMaxInProgressProposals(uint16).notice: Set the max number of concurrent InProgress proposals

setVotingPeriod(uint256).notice: Set the voting period for a Governance proposal

setVotingQuorumPercent(uint256).notice: Set the voting quorum percentage for a Governance proposal

submitProposal(bytes32,uint256,string,by.notice: Submit a proposal for vote. Only callable by addresses with non-zero total active stake.     total active stake = total active deployer stake + total active delegator stake

submitVote(uint256,uint8).notice: Vote on an active Proposal. Only callable by addresses with non-zero active stake.

updateVote(uint256,uint8).notice: Update previous vote on an active Proposal. Only callable by addresses with non-zero active stake.

vetoProposal(uint256).notice: Action limited to the guardian address that can veto a proposal
